<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1050,1939]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1050,1075]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum yellow with black marks and conspicuous median yellow stripe. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1371,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
) with pair of anteromedian diagonal black arches connected to each other medially; posterior half with mosaic. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
) with pair of lateral yellow arches anteriorly convergent, bordered by black lines. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1428,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
) pinkish-red with dark brown veins; clavus with irregular narrow bluish-white stripe adjacent to claval commissure; claval sulcus with dark brown stripe bordered by white stripes; costal area with two adjacent longitudinal stripes, innermost white and outermost dark brown; apex gray. Face (
<figureCitation box="[841,922,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
) yellow with black marks. Frons with mosaic of rounded areas bordered by black; dorsally with narrow transverse yellow stripe slightly sinuous. Male pygofer posteriorly concave, long and broad posterodorsal process with apex acute, inner long and tapered ventroapical spine, medially directed. Paraphyses asymmetrical, basal plate V-shaped, right ramus long and broad, left ramus long and moderately narrow. Aedeagal shaft curved ventrally on apical half, paired hook-shaped basiventral processes directed to right side, anteriorly curved. Female sternite VII with pair of lateral large black areas; shape similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[354,479,1447,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis box="[354,479,1447,1471]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[658,741,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
) with broad sclerotized plate, anteriorly bilobate and deeply notched medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1050,1939]" box="[199,597,1518,1543]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
Female length. 
<quantity box="[372,507,1518,1543]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.05" metricValueMax="9.6" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" unit="mm" value="9.05" valueMax="9.6" valueMin="8.5">8.5–9.6 mm</quantity>
(n = 3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1050,1939]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,576,1554,1579]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[928,1053,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis box="[928,1053,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1315,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with broad, bilobate sclerotized plate; anterior margin with deep and narrow median notch; posterior margin with pair of lateral subtrapezoidal prominences. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[827,913,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
) similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[1142,1256,1627,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dampfi">
<emphasis box="[1142,1256,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. dampfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; disc with thin macrosetae on central portion, posterodorsal portion and apical 2/3 of posteroventral portion with long macrosetae, posterodorsal margin and apex of posteroventral margin with row of short macrosetae. Valvula I, in ventral view, with basal portion similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[559,679,1734,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krameri">
<emphasis box="[559,679,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. krameri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; blade similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[960,1081,1735,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[960,1081,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; teeth, on median portion (
<figureCitation box="[547,631,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
), triangular and elongate, moderately prominent, 3–4 times longer than high, almost not spaced from one another; preapical prominence approximately aligned to anteapical tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
